social_posts.post_text: happy Saturday lovely people ! 💌 lots going on here in Florida recently with preparations for competitions, auditions, and our winter shows 🎄🩰 I’m super excited to be dancing in Florida Classical Ballet’s Holiday Gala on Dec 10th and FCB’s Nutcracker on Dec 11th! If you’re in south Florida on either of those days and would like to come see me dance you can purchase tickets via the link in my bio! I hope to see some familiar faces in the audience :) #ballerina #ballet #getthemagalymagic💫

holiday gala x nutcracker post 🎄💌 I love ballet and I’m so lucky that I get to do what I love with such lovely people :) endless thanks to my incredible director and coach @magalysuarez_ballet for always believing in me and showing me that I’m capable of more than I realize <33 #getthemagalymagic💫 #nutcrackerballet

My heart is so full of gratitude and love for everyone who helped make 2022 such a special year for me 💌 I owe this year and all of its successes to all of my teachers, coaches, colleagues and friends who have been nothing but supportive of me and my journey in this art form <3 I’m so excited to see how 2023 unwraps 🩰

Big news to go along with this post !! I’m incredibly excited to share that next season I will be joining Tulsa Ballet II !!!! I am so excited to begin this new chapter in my career and I’m so grateful to have been given this opportunity <33 I have so many people to thank, my family, all of my teachers and coaches, my friends and supporters; but I really want to take the time to express my gratitude for YAGP on this one 🫶🏻 at YAGP in 2018 Larissa put me in contact, for the first time, with my incredible coach and mentor Magaly Suarez. At NYC finals in 2019 I met Ernst Meisner and was given a position at the Dutch National Ballet Academy where I graduated from in 2021. This past weekend at YAGP Toronto I took a master class with Marcello Angelini and was offered my contract for Tulsa Ballet II 💌 It’s hard to express how lucky I feel for all of these opportunities and if it were not for YAGP I would not have had any of them. I remember watching First Position when I was 12 and thinking that I would probably never reach that level in ballet and so all of this has really been a full circle moment for me. Here’s to a new chapter 🥳 #getthemagalymagic💫 #yagp #ballerina

thank you so much to @telmo_gomes_moreira for this beautiful pas de deux and thank you to @th3_luke for being so wonderful to dance with 🫶🏻 my heart is full !! #pasdedeux #usaibc
